[2] Samoa: deaths
Date: Sat 7 Dec 2019
Source: Newshub [edited]
https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2019/12/samoan-measles-crisis-death-toll-continues-to-rise.html


Samoa measles deaths rise to 65 with 4460 cases 18 children are critically ill. Approximately 89% of all eligible people have been vaccinated.

The death toll in the Samoan measles crisis continues to raise, with 2 more fatalities in the last 24 hours. In a statement, the Samoan government confirmed a total of 65 deaths since the outbreak started. "The Ministry of Health confirms a total of 4460 measles cases have been reported to the Disease Surveillance Team, since the outbreak started. There were 103 recorded in the last 24 hours."

There are currently 165 patients in health facilities receiving treatment, including 18 critically ill children and 3 pregnant women.

The Ministry of Health said the total number of measles cases admitted to all hospitals is 1407. Of that, 1177 patients have been discharged.

The statement said that as of 6 Dec 2019, approximately 89% of all eligible people in Samoa have been vaccinated against measles. The estimated vaccination coverage in Samoa is 85% of targeted infants and children aged 6 months to 4 years old and 96% of targeted children aged 5-19.

[Byline: Rachel Sadler]

